<DocsPageTitle Path="Helpers/Enums">
    Blazorise enums
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Learn about Blazorise enums and how to use them to keep UI behavior and styling consistent.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Enums provide a shared vocabulary for sizing, alignment, placement, and component behavior so you can express intent without custom CSS or ad-hoc strings.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    How it works
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Pick the enum that matches the component parameter you are configuring, then assign the value directly in your markup.
    For example, choose placement enums for tooltips, alignment enums for text, and sizing enums for components.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Examples
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Typical enum usage looks like:
</DocsPageParagraph>

<UnorderedList>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>ButtonType.Submit</Code> to submit a form.</UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>TextAlignment.Center</Code> to center-align text.</UnorderedListItem>
    <UnorderedListItem><Code>TooltipPlacement.Top</Code> to place a tooltip above its target.</UnorderedListItem>
</UnorderedList>

